headlines.description: Darron Thomas passed for three touchdowns and ran for another, and top-ranked Oregon earned at least a share of a second consecutive Pac-10 title with a 48-29 victory over No. 20 Arizona on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 Ducks pull away from Arizona

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Cam Newton threw for three touchdowns and ran for another, leading No. 2 Auburn back from a 24-point deficit Saturday for a stunning 28-27 victory over No. 9 Alabama that kept the Tigers on course for a shot at the national championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newton takes charge in Auburn's rally

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: Anthony Martinez kicked a 34-yard field goal in overtime Friday night, capping a Nevada comeback that gave the Wolf Pack a 34-31 win over previously unbeaten Boise State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise St.'s BCS dream dashed in OT

headlines.description: Running back Rex Burkhead passed for two touchdowns and ran for 101 yards and another score, and No. 16 Nebraska clinched the Big 12 North with a 45-17 victory over Colorado on Friday in their final meeting before they head to different conferences.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nebraska whips Colorado, wins Big 12 North

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Bilal Powell scored three times as Louisville routed Rutgers on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: A Strong effort: Louisville qualifies for bowl

events.name: Ohio Bobcats at Kent State Golden Flashes
West Virginia Mountaineers at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Brandon Hogan's interception and fumble recovery led to touchdowns in the first half and West Virginia upset Backyard Brawl rival Pittsburgh for the second straight season, winning 35-10 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pitt plays way out of BCS contention

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Eastern Michigan Eagles

headlines.description: Jordan Lynch rushed 142 yards and scored two touchdowns and Northern Illinois beat Eastern Michigan 71-3 Friday in the last game of the regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: N. Illinois routs E.MU to go unbeaten in MAC

events.name: SMU Mustangs at East Carolina Pirates

headlines.description: Zach Line scored on a short touchdown run in overtime and Richard Crawford followed with the game-ending interception to help Southern Methodist beat East Carolina 45-38 on Friday, clinching a spot in the Conference USA championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: SMU takes West, secures spot for C-USA title

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Bowling Green Falcons
Central Michigan Chippewas at Toledo Rockets
UCLA Bruins at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Backup Brock Osweiler threw for 380 yards and hit Aaron Pflugrad on two of his four touchdown passes, helping Arizona State keep its slim bowl hopes alive with a 55-34 victory over UCLA on Friday.

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at Tulsa Golden Hurricane
